  <div class="wrap prose">
    <h2>A father and son who know these vehicles</h2>
    <p>Stuart Gilbert Landrovers has grown up around one make. Stuart started out on Land Rovers and never moved on to anything else, and David has worked alongside him for years — so between the two of us there's more than seventy-five years of hands on these vehicles. That's not a marketing line. It's why a customer can describe a noise down the phone and one of us usually knows where to look before the Land Rover's even on the ramp.</p>

    <h2>How a visit works</h2>
    <p>We run by appointment, so the first step is always a phone call. When you ring, you'll get Stuart or David — not a service desk, not a booking system. We'll talk through what the vehicle's doing, give you an honest idea of what's involved, and book it in. When you collect it, it's the same two people handing the keys back. Nothing gets passed down a line of technicians who've never met you.</p>

    <h2>Honest work, fair rates</h2>
    <p>We're an independent specialist, not a main dealer, and we charge accordingly. We tell you what needs doing now, what can wait, and what it will cost before we start. If something turns out to be simpler than feared, that's reflected in the bill. A proper independent Land Rover garage is getting harder to find in Kent — we intend to stay one.</p>

    <blockquote class="pull">
      <p>If it's got a green oval on the bonnet, we've probably had one in.</p>
      <cite>Stuart Gilbert</cite>
    </blockquote>

    <p>From Series trucks to the latest Defender, Range Rovers, Discoverys, Freelanders and everything in between — if it's a Land Rover, it's what we do. Give us a ring on <a href="tel:{{ site.phoneTel }}">{{ site.phoneDisplay }}</a> and we'll be glad to help.</p>
